SIMPLE: iced
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iced
<hw>Iced</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧st)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Covered with ice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Chilled with ice; <as>as, <ex>iced</ex> water;
<ex>iced</ex> tea; <ex>iced</ex> coffee</as>; -- of beverages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>Covered with something
resembling ice, as sugar icing; frosted; <as>as, <ex>iced</ex>
cake</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Iced cream</b></col>. <cd>Same as <cref>Ice cream</cref>,
under <er>Ice</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Icefall</ent>⟦br⟧
